Key differences between EMR vendors and billing companies

Area
EMR Vendors
Primrose
Advantage
Credentialing
No EMR vendors do not do credentialing leaving the practice to fend for themselves. During the startup phase, a clinic could lose tens of thousands for each month they are out-of-network.
Yes Typically, billing companies will do credentialing for a nominal cost. They are knowledgeable on credentialing with the top insurance companies. This alone can be result in your practice reaching breakeven months ahead of an EMR vendor
Billing Companies
Statements
Maybe Check if your EMR vendor will mail out patient statements and how much it costs
Yes Patient statements are typically included at no additional cost
Billing Companies
Appeals
Level-1 EMR vendors lack the expertise to appeal based on specialty. Appeals are basic and automated.
Level-2 Billing companies AR members specialize in their own domain and gain expertise in appeals. We also appeal multiple times when necessary.
Billing Companies
Check depositing
No You or your office manager will need to take the checks to the bank
Yes Billing companies typically deposit your check saving you trips to your bank and standing in line
Billing Companies
Patient calls
No EMR vendors require the clinic staff to take the calls
Yes Billing companies typically handle all incoming patient calls with questions on balance and take payments over the phone
Billing Companies
Skillset
Software Key skills and focus of EMR vendors is building software.
Billing Services Billing service companies focus on billing and maximizing revenue for clients.
Billing Companies
Support
Customer Service EMR vendors have a customer service team that are impersonal and are not familiar with your account.
Individual Biller Typically, you will be assigned one biller and they will be familiar with all aspects of your practice.
Billing Companies
Conflicts
Often outside vendor Most EMR vendors contract with an outside billing company. Their interests are different and the client suffers. Most practices switch to a dedicated billing company for this reason.
Internal Team We are first and foremost a billing company. We only build technologies that maximize collection for our clients.
Billing Companies
Mail processing
No Your staff will need to spend hours processing mail and then scanning them in
Yes We set up a dropbox to receive and process all incoming mail including EOBS
